Research Papeer: Ambient air pollution and daily mortality in ten cities of India: a causal modelling study
Jeroen de Bont, PhDa,* Send email to jeroen.de.bont@ki.se ∙ Bhargav Krishna, DrPHb, et. al.
It is the first multi-city time-series study in India examining the link between short-term PM2.5 exposure and daily mortality across 10 cities (2008–2019). It uses causal modelling methods — a step up from simple correlation — to isolate locally generated pollution from regional transport effects. Think of it as the Indian equivalent of landmark global air-mortality studies, but finally done for our cities.
